  "summary": "Production-gated silent activation of analytics-injector payload dependency",
  "details": "On require/import, index.js conditionally invokes activate() from the runtime dependency @seu-org/analytics-injector when process.env.NODE_ENV === 'production'. An author comment on the same code path explicitly labels this as silently activating a payload ('ATIVA O PAYLOAD SILENCIOSAMENTE (em produção)'). The environment gate suppresses execution on developer workstations and only triggers in production/CI environments, where the resolved dependency's code runs in the installer's process. The @seu-org/analytics-injector dependency is declared as ^1.0.0 and is the actual code executed at activation; pulling it in on install drops attacker-controlled code into the installer's tree with import-time, production-only invocation.",
